summary:: Register actions to be taken to initialise a basic tree of groups on the server
related:: Classes/Server, Classes/ServerQuit, Classes/ServerBoot, Classes/CmdPeriod

description::

The singleton ServerTree provides a place for registering functions and objects for events that should happen when a given server has booted and when all synths are freed.
This is to initialise a basic tree of groups on the server.

See link::Classes/AbstractServerAction:: for usage.

